laboratory_examinations.findings: Hepatic steatosis noted. The liver enhances homogeneously, without focal lesions. Gallbladder normal, without radiopaque stones. The portal vein is patent. No ascites or biliary duct dilation. A 1.7 cm simple cyst is noted in the midpole of the left kidney. Mid appendix is mildly dilated up to 10 mm and fluid-filled, minimal surrounding fat stranding. Free pelvic fluid identified.
